7665588,s6,T12,T28,It has been suggested that the ,ubiquitin,-,proteasome," system is involved in the process; however, the specific enzymes involved and the mechanism of limited proteolysis, in which half of the molecule is spared, have been obscure.",Not_a_complex

7665588,s10,T14,T15,"In this study, we demonstrate reconstitution of a cell-free processing system and demonstrate directly that: (a) the ",ubiquitin,-proteasome system is involved in processing of the intact ,p105," precursor, (b) conjugation of ubiquitin to the precursor is an essential intermediate step in the processing, (c) the recently discovered novel species of the ubiquitin-carrier protein, E2-F1, that is involved in the conjugation and degradation of p53, is also required for the limited processing of the p105 precursor, and (d) a novel, approximately 320-kDa species of ubiquitin-protein ligase, is involved in the process.",Not_a_complex
